Step Four: Align Sales and Marketing Around a Shared Revenue Goal
One of the most persistent problems in B2B GTM execution is the gap between marketing and sales. Marketing generates leads. Sales complains about lead quality. Marketing says sales is not following up. The cycle continues and revenue suffers.

In 2026, this dynamic is no longer acceptable. Aligned teams see 60% higher win rates and 72% stronger customer engagement, underscoring how unified go-to-market motions outperform fragmented ones.

The solution is to move to a RevOps model where marketing, sales, and customer success share data, accountability, and metrics. Instead of measuring marketing success by MQL volume, measure it by pipeline contribution, influenced revenue, and win rates on marketing-sourced deals. Instead of evaluating sales on activity metrics alone, evaluate their ability to move qualified opportunities through the funnel efficiently.

What does practical sales and marketing alignment look like?

A shared definition of what constitutes a qualified lead
A documented lead handoff process with clear SLAs
Regular joint pipeline reviews between marketing and sales leadership
Shared access to intent data and account engagement insights
Unified reporting that shows the full revenue journey from first touch to closed deal
When sales and marketing operate from the same playbook, GTM execution becomes dramatically more efficient and effective.

Step Five: Leverage Intent Data to Prioritize and Personalize at Scale
Not all potential buyers are equal. Some are actively researching solutions right now. Others are months away from a buying decision. Treating them the same way wastes budget and alienates prospects who are not yet ready to engage.

Intent data changes the equation. By tracking behavioral signals across the web, including content consumption, search queries, competitor comparisons, and review site visits, intent data platforms allow you to identify which accounts are showing active buying signals and prioritize your GTM outreach accordingly.

